  "description": [
    "V A w STURZO SCRAPS ARE WEAKENING MUSSOLINI HOLD ROME The recent differences be tween Mussolinis Fascism and the Catholic party of Italy or Popolari are due to more than mere personal squabbles of Mussolini and Don Sturzo Back of these differences stands a fundamental issue which is as old as the quarrels between tyran ny and popular government Mussolini wants a centralized gov ernment for the purpose of pursuing the aims of militarism and imperial ism The Popolari want as much de centralization and democratic poli tics as is compatible with capitalist business on a liberal scale Don Sturzo the Italian Catholic leader has long worked to form an international of liberal capitalists for the purpose of bringing about peace and cooperation in international re lations Defeated Socialist Party If any single cause can be credited with the defeat of Italian Socialism the credit must go not to Mussolini and his Fascisti but to Don Sturzo and his Popolari The Popolari party like Fascism is an afterwar product It was organ ized by the liberal bourgeoisie of Italy with the pronounced intention of preventing the Italian Socialist party from reaping the benefits of the popular disappointments due to the"
